{
	"version": {
		"string": "@VERSION@",
		"year": @YEAR@
	},
	"title": "Multithreaded minor-GC stability fix",
	"files": {
		"html_template": "readme.in.html",
		"html_out": "readme.html",
		"markdown_out": "readme.md",
		"openai_token": "openai_api_key.dat"
	},
	"features": [
		{
			"version": "v2026.6.4",
			"items": [
				"VM: fixed an intermittent multithreaded crash in the generational minor garbage collector — a thread being spawned held its self/param as untracked pointers, so a moving collection during the spawn handoff could leave the new thread a stale reference; these are now tracked and relocated across collection"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2026.6.3",
			"items": [
				"VM: generational minor garbage collection is now enabled — nursery-full collections scan only the remembered set plus roots and recycle the nursery without sweeping old gen, with a major-GC fallback under old-gen pressure; JIT and interpreter reference stores emit the write barrier on AMD64 and ARM64",
				"Language: closure ergonomics — call a FuncRef directly with v(), bare lambdas with an inferred return type (\\() => x) that auto-wrap into FuncRef<R> in assignments, returns, method arguments, and collection elements, and lambda block bodies",
				"Fixes: multi-capture closure heap corruption (closure-local capture ids); ARM64 negative-offset JIT load/stores (signed LDUR/STUR)"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2026.6.2",
			"items": [
				"Documentation: API reference code examples now render as formatted, syntax-highlighted blocks — the ONNX library examples previously appeared as run-on inline text",
				"Tooling: the release-process skills (version bump, release, docs, playground deploy) are now versioned in the repo"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2026.6.1",
			"items": [
				"Language: string interpolation with expressions and format specifiers (\"{$pi:.2}\", \"{$total * rate}\") plus String->Format positional templating",
				"Language: generics with bounds, F-bounds, and declaration-site variance (out/in covariance/contravariance)",
				"VM: cooperative multithreaded stop-the-world garbage collection with JIT safepoints on AMD64 and ARM64",
				"Debugger: major command-line (obd) and VS Code (DAP) upgrade — frame navigation, locals, set-variable, method/conditional/temporary breakpoints, watchpoints, function breakpoints, logpoints, in-process restart, and exception breakpoints",
				"Security: TLS and DTLS clients verify server certificates by default; hardened untrusted-input deserialization",
				"Libraries: new Web.Server HTTP library; reproducible byte-identical .obl builds",
				"Fixes: serialization correctness (64-bit ints and Int[], function-reference fields); compiler LICM/ConstantProp; macOS ONNX CoreML cache (~35x faster warm starts)"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2026.6.0",
			"items": [
				"Compiler: Tail Call Optimization (TCO) — self-recursive tail calls rewritten to jumps, eliminating stack growth (-opt s1+)",
				"Compiler: Loop-Invariant Code Motion (LICM) — hoists arr->Size() reads and pure arithmetic out of loop bodies (-opt s2+)",
				"VM: Auto-JIT now compiles methods containing MTHD_CALL after 10 invocations (5-15% speedup across benchmarks)",
				"VM: Extended interpreter fast-path with 15 additional inline opcodes (comparisons, bitwise, shifts, logical)",
				"Performance: bench_matrix_multiply -14%, bench_dead_code -15%, bench_array_intensive -12%, binarytrees -7%, mandelbrot -6%"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2024.10.0",
			"items": [
				"Fixed bugs #501 and #503"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2024.9.0",
			"items": [
				"Added library support for JSON-RPC",
				"Code generation optimized to eliminate redundant labels",
				"Added trim front and back to the 'System.String'",
				"Refactored the 'Collections.Stack' class to be list vs. array based",
				"Fixed bugs #501 and #502"
			]
		},
		{
			"version": "v2024.8.1",
			"items": [
				"Support for strings in select statement",
				"Bug fixes",
				"\tFixed REPL start up issues",
				"\tCode refactoring for performance"
			]
		}
	]
}